message.content:
The image is a binary, black and white diagram of an inverted pyramid resembling a diamond shape. The structure has six points in total. From top to bottom, there are three smaller triangular shapes with sharp points that converge at the center to form a hexagon. 

A long, narrow triangle-shaped slice is cut out of it, with one point on either end and the remaining area filled more densely than the rest. This cut creates an opening in two places along its length due to the number of points being a multiple of three. A distinct line forms between these two openings in the center.

The entire image is reflected as if in a mirror or water surface, adding another layer of symmetry to this intriguing abstract design. Despite its simplicity, it's a complex geometric formation that plays with shapes and spaces in an interesting way.
